column10:
Important little update from October 2019. You see those minimum and recommended RAM numbers? Well, those are BULLHOCKEY. My friend's save no longer loads with 8 gb RAM, so you need at least 12 gb. I'm THIS CLOSE to changing this review to negative. Every update breaks something and you hope that it's not your savegame.



This game initially released with quite a lot of multiplayer bugs and even some single player ones, but I still totally recommend it. Especially since those bugs are being rapidly fixed. Single player is already perfect. Multiplayer is getting there.
It's a really zen make-your-own-adventure-sandbox type of game with no fauna or weapons and exploration of most planets being repetitive, but entertaining nonetheless. Adventures include, but are not limited to:

- Building a really neat optimized base on terrain that is not level and managing it's power levels... that is until you get an RTG;
- Exploring a vast planet with only a compass in hands to find all structures and [Collect all the garbage!];
- Optionally digging your rover out of a newly discovered 30 meter deep trench in the middle of said exploration;
- Trying to guess which items to bring to a new planet to optimize base building time. Spoilers: don't worry about that too much, the game is forgiving;
- Exploring the technology... tree? More like list, actually. All items unlock independently;
- Drilling straight down for 3 minutes in a large expensive vehicle that you intend to return to the surface;
- Optionally building an underground base and returning said vehicle to surface in the span of 2-4 hours (depends on whether you have a trailer);
- Frantically looking for your own dead body or nearest tether line in some spooky unfamiliar caverns. Seriously, they shouldn't add a map, we would lose half the fun;
- Making a makeshift rocket league field;
- Oh, and actually attempting to finish the game. Supposedly it has an ending.

By the way, the whole experience is very reminiscent of LEGO™, you should totally try it out. Can't wait for the Wanderers Update for even more content.


UPD. I got crashed and killed 4 times in a multiplayer session. The last one was in space. Screw this mess.


